  "text": "For a diagnostic or predictive test, the sensitivity (true positives) and specificity (1-false positive) are correlated; therefore, it is not correct to estimate these two quantities independently. To bypass this problem, the SROC method was used. The SROC curve is estimated by the regression D=A+BS, where D is the difference of the logits of the true-positive and false-positive rate, and S is the sum of these logits [CITATION_1] ). The SROC curve shows the balance between sensitivity and specificity across the included studies.",
